            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-10T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-10T09:00:00-05:00" n="463" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/12–1045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-10T17:00:00+03:00">December 10, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4126. Proposal to initiate discussions between British and Soviet Governments
                    with object of coordinating plans for withdrawal of Soviet and British troops
                    from Iran at earliest possible date made in letter to Molotov on December 8 by
                    British Ambassador Moscow.</p>
                <p>Proposal based on exchange of correspondence between Bevin and Molotov at London
                    ForMin meeting and specific reference made to Molotov’s letter to Bevin of
                    September 20 agreeing to discuss if necessary toward end of period specified in
                    treaty of alliance between Soviet Union, Great Britain and Iran plan for final
                    withdrawal of British and Soviet troops.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 4126. Repeated Tehran 174. Repeated London 628.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
